  "description": "The Ouroboros strange attractor determines how far Oracle's GENDY waveform steps each synthesis cycle — high chaos index drives large stochastic leaps; low chaos (attractor collapsed near a fixed point) produces tiny trembling steps that hover around a single frequency. The prophecy's pace is dictated by the geometry of chaos. At low ouro_leash the attractor roams freely and Oracle stutters and leaps across maqam intervals unpredictably. Tighten the leash to restrain both systems simultaneously: the attractor converges and the GENDY waveform settles into a narrow timbral band. The oracle speaks more slowly when the strange attractor is caged.",
